<concept id="c_culture">
    <title>Culture</title>
    <shortdesc>Information on main culture events in Krakow</shortdesc>
    <conbody>
        <p>Kraków was named the official <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Capital_of_Culture" format="html"
                scope="external">European Capital of Culture</xref> for the year 2000 by the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union" format="html" scope="external"
                >European Union</xref>.<sup><xref
                    href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krak%C3%B3w#cite_note-European_Capital_of_Culture_in_Poland_again-192"
                    format="html" scope="external">[191]</xref></sup> It is a major attraction for
            both local and international tourists, attracting nearly 13 million visitors a
                    year.<sup><xref href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krak%C3%B3w#cite_note-193"
                    format="html" scope="external">[192]</xref></sup> Major landmarks include the
                <xref href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Market_Square,_Krak%C3%B3w"
                format="html" scope="external">Main Market Square</xref> with <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._Mary%27s_Basilica,_Krak%C3%B3w"
                format="html" scope="external">St. Mary's Basilica</xref> and the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sukiennice" format="html" scope="external"
                >Sukiennice Cloth Hall</xref>, the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wawel_Castle" format="html" scope="external"
                >Wawel Castle</xref>, the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Museum,_Krak%C3%B3w" format="html"
                scope="external">National Art Museum</xref>, the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zygmunt_(bell)" format="html" scope="external"
                >Zygmunt Bell</xref> at the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wawel_Cathedral" format="html" scope="external"
                >Wawel Cathedral</xref>, and the medieval <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._Florian%27s_Gate" format="html"
                scope="external">St. Florian's Gate</xref> with the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krak%C3%B3w_barbican" format="html"
                scope="external">Barbican</xref> along the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Road,_Krak%C3%B3w" format="html"
                scope="external">Royal Coronation Route</xref>.<sup><xref
                    href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krak%C3%B3w#cite_note-krakow-info-194"
                    format="html" scope="external">[193]</xref></sup> Kraków has 28 museums and
                <xref href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_art" format="html" scope="external"
                >public art</xref> galleries. Among them is the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Czartoryski_Museum" format="html"
                scope="external">Czartoryski Museum</xref> featuring works by <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonardo_da_Vinci" format="html"
                scope="external">Leonardo da Vinci</xref> and <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rembrandt" format="html" scope="external"
                >Rembrandt</xref> as well as the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EUROPEUM_-_European_Culture_Centre"
                format="html" scope="external">EUROPEUM - European Culture Centre</xref> and the
                <xref href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archaeological_Museum_of_Krak%C3%B3w"
                format="html" scope="external">Archaeological Museum of Kraków</xref> whose
            collection highlights include the <xref href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zbruch_Idol"
                format="html" scope="external">Zbruch Idol</xref> and the <xref
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bronocice_pot" format="html" scope="external"
                >Bronocice Pot</xref>.</p>
    </conbody>
